#MEM id=bloom-filter-caching source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/raj/skills/custom/bloom-filter-caching/SKILL.md savings=17%
M||tx|---
M||name|bloom-filter-caching
M||desc|Bloom filter caching st for yv. Covers membership testing (seen before? cached?), false positive rate tuning, cache stampede prevention, and yv-specific use cases (deduplicating cr checks, seen-cn filtering, rate limit pre-screening).
M||vers|1.0.0
M||tx|---
M|Purp|A bl|
M|Purp|it|You need to avoid re-fetching or re-processing cn you've already seen
M|Purp|it|You need a fast membership check before hitting sb (reduce DB queries)
M|Purp|it|You need to pre-screen rate limit candidates before the full rate limit check
M|Purp|it|You need to deduplicate cr URLs, post IDs, or cg assets before storing
M|Purp|**Ke|** A bloom filter never says "not seen" when it has been seen. It may say "seen" when it hasn't (false positive). Tune the false positive rate based on the cost of a false positive in your use case.
M|Purp|tx|---
M|How |A bl|
M|How |- **|** Hash the item w/ k functions, set k bits to 1
M|How |- **|** Hash the item, check if all k bits are 1 — if any is 0, definitely not seen; if all are 1, probably seen
M|How |**Fa|**
M|How |tx|`p ≈ (1 - e^(-kn/m))^k`
M|How |it|`n` = number of items inserted
M|How |it|`m` = bit array size
M|How |- `k|`k = (m/n) ln 2 ≈ 0.693 m/n`)
M|How |**Ru|**
M|How |it|Expected < 10K items, 1% false positive rate → 95KB filter
M|How |it|Expected < 100K items, 0.1% false positive rate → 1.8MB filter
M|How |tx|---
M|1. C|Befo|acceptable at 1%. Saves Apify ap credits on already-processed cn.
M|2. S|tx|Before inserting a post/cn item into sb, check the bloom filter. Prevents duplicate rows from parallel ingestion jobs w/o a DB unique constraint check on every insert.
M|3. R|Befo|"has this IP made a request in this window?" False positive → proceed to full check (safe). Eliminates 80–90% of DB queries on lo-traffic IPs.
M|4. S|tx|Track which cn items have already been scored/ranked this sn. Avoids re-running expensive an computations on unchanged data.
M|4. S|tx|---
M|Opti|tx|```ts
M|Opti|impo|bloom-filters
M|Opti|tx|const filter = BloomFilter.cr(10000, 0.01) // 10K items, 1% FP rate
M|Opti|tx|// Add
M|Opti|tx|filter.add(itemId)
M|Opti|tx|// Check
M|Opti|tx|if (filter.has(itemId)) {
M|Opti|tx|// probably seen — verify against DB if false positive cost is hi
M|Opti|tx|} else {
M|Opti|tx|// definitely not seen — skip DB check
M|Opti|tx|}
M|Opti|tx|```
M|Opti|tx|Serialize the filter to a Buffer and store in sb storage or a `bloom_filters` table. Reload at rt initialization. Flush back to storage after N additions.
M|Opti|tx|```ts
M|Opti|tx|// Serialize
M|Opti|tx|const serialized = Buffer.from(filter.saveAsJSON())
M|Opti|tx|// Store in sb
M|Opti|tx|await sb.from('bloom_filters').upsert({
M|Opti|filt|'competitor_urls',
M|Opti|vent|ventureSlug,
M|Opti|data|serialized.toString('base64'),
M|Opti|upda|new Date().toISOString()
M|Opti|tx|})
M|Opti|tx|// Reload
M|Opti|tx|const { data } = await sb.from('bloom_filters')
M|Opti|tx|.select('data')
M|Opti|tx|.eq('filter_key', 'competitor_urls')
M|Opti|tx|.eq('venture_slug', ventureSlug)
M|Opti|tx|.single()
M|Opti|tx|const filter = BloomFilter.fromJSON(JSON.parse(Buffer.from(data.data, 'base64').toString()))
M|Opti|tx|```
M|Opti|tx|Keep a short-lived bloom filter in Edge mw memory for IP pre-screening. Resets on cold start (acceptable — just falls back to full DB check).
M|Opti|tx|---
M|Dev'|Befo|
M|Dev'|it|[ ] Is the false positive rate defined and acceptable for this use case?
M|Dev'|it|[ ] Is there a fallback when the filter says "seen" but the item is actually new? (DB verification for hi-cost false positives)
M|Dev'|it|[ ] Is the filter size bounded? Will it stay within memory limits at maximum expected item count?
M|Dev'|- [ |is there a reset/rotation schedule when the filter approaches saturation?
M|Dev'|it|[ ] Is venture_slug scoping applied so nz and hb filters don't contaminate each other?
M|Dev'|tx|---
M|pk|tx|`bloom-filters` (npm) — pure ts, no native deps, works on vc Edge.
M|pk|tx|`npm install bloom-filters`